<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Tailwind CDN Example</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com" defer></script>

    <style type="text/tailwindcss">
      @layer utilities {
        .content-auto {
          content-visibility: auto;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-gray-100 p-4">
    <div
      class="max-w-md mx-auto bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md overflow-hidden md:max-w-2xl"
    >
      <div class="md:flex">
        <div class="md:shrink-0">
          <img
            class="h-48 w-full object-cover md:h-full md:w-48"
            src="https://source.unsplash.com/random/400x400"
            alt="Modern building architecture"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div
            class="uppercase tracking-wide text-sm text-indigo-500 font-semibold"
          >
            Company retreats
          </div>
          <a
            href="#"
            class="block mt-1 text-lg leading-tight font-medium text-black hover:underline"
            >Finding amazing places to stay productive</a
          >
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-500">
            Looking to take your team away on a retreat to a remote location? We
            cover some important aspects to consider.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-200 rounded">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Another Section</h2>
      <p class="text-blue-700">
        This section demonstrates more Tailwind utility classes. For example,
        the background color and text colors.
      </p>
      <button
        class="mt-4 bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded"
        >Click Me</button
      >
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-green-200 rounded">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">
        Custom tailwind style
      </h2>
      <p class="text-green-700 content-auto">
        Using the style tag, we can add custom tailwind styles. Here,
        content-auto is added.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
